WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.475
Cyberattacks are inevitable.

00:00:02.475 --> 00:00:06.060
No matter how many security controls and defenses you have,

00:00:06.060 --> 00:00:11.190
someone is bound to breach security and you have to be prepared for that.

00:00:11.190 --> 00:00:14.685
How you respond makes all the difference.

00:00:14.685 --> 00:00:17.460
This lesson focuses on what you need to

00:00:17.460 --> 00:00:21.615
know to follow and activate an incident response plan.

00:00:21.615 --> 00:00:24.330
By the end of this lesson: You'll be able

00:00:24.330 --> 00:00:28.334
to explain the relationship between incident response,

00:00:28.334 --> 00:00:31.795
disaster recovery, and business continuity;

00:00:31.795 --> 00:00:35.060
You'll be able to distinguish events from

00:00:35.060 --> 00:00:39.160
incidents and recognize indicators of compromise;

00:00:39.160 --> 00:00:44.810
You'll also learn to explain the incident response lifecycle; And finally,

00:00:44.810 --> 00:00:47.960
recognize the key incident response team roles

00:00:47.960 --> 00:00:52.260
and core components of an incident response plan.

